From: Gentoo
Subject: Remove unused implicit event loop lookup from async test
Upstream: not submitted; test-only Python 3.14 compatibility fix

Python 3.14 no longer implicitly creates an event loop in
asyncio.get_event_loop().  The returned loop was unused because the actual
network send is intentionally commented out, so the lookup is unrelated to
what this offline test covers.

--- a/tests/test_webhook.py
+++ b/tests/test_webhook.py
@@ -40,9 +40,6 @@ def test_async_send_message():
     This asynchronously send a simple text message with a title and link button.
     """
 
-    # loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
-    _ = asyncio.get_event_loop()
-
     teams_message = pymsteams.async_connectorcard(os.getenv("MS_TEAMS_WEBHOOK"))
     teams_message.text("This is a simple text message.")
     teams_message.title("Simple Message Title")
